    "diffSummary": "Made the desktop app log in / listen without putting the bearer token in the webview. command/ adds cred_file_summary, login_from_file, and start_listening_from_file, which read a fixed repo-local session file (env ZALO_CRED_FILE or repo-root .zalo-cred.json) — the UI supplies no path, so arbitrary file reads are not possible. login/listen logic was refactored into a shared login_and_listen helper. The frontend (+page.svelte) now uses buttons (Check session / Log in / Log in + listen) instead of a credential textarea, so imei/cookie/userAgent never enter the DOM. Verified live: the core read .zalo-cred.json (8 cookies, vi) and logged in (uid_len=19, display name present), and GUI login as the real account was confirmed via tauri dev. Added a src-tauri/tauri.dev-npm.conf.json helper so tauri dev can run with npm (bun not installed). Offline tests cover the fixed-path guarantee and the value-free missing-file error.",
    "changedFiles": [
        "src-tauri/src/command/mod.rs",
        "src-tauri/src/lib.rs",
        "src/routes/+page.svelte",
        "src-tauri/tauri.dev-npm.conf.json"
    ],
